Locations.First gate:
The first gate:
{{Quote|''...lies hidden upon the back of the mountains, where the ice and rocks touch the summer sky of [[Amaunator]]'s belt.''}}
[[Amaunator's belt]] was a constellation appearing in the summer over the [[Spine of the World]]. The gate was within a deep cave and was guarded by a vain and greedy [[white dragon]], who demanded a hefty fee to allow anyone past.

Locations.Second gate:
The texts stated that the second gate was:
{{Quote|''...north of [[Novularond]], shining bright upon [[Misken's Peak]] at [[Highsummer]].''}}
Misken's Peak was since demolished by the [[Great Glacier]] and the portal buried beneath the ice.

Locations.Third gate:
According to the texts, the third gate was on:
{{Quote|''...Andrio's Peak near the Garden of Eldath.''}}
The name of the peak was a misspelling by a scribe and should have referred to [[Mount Andrus]]. The garden referred to [[Cedarsproke]], a city in the [[Gulthmere Forest]].
